00:04:42.800 --> 00:04:44.033
Water is H2O.

00:04:46.400 --> 00:04:51.433
The molecular weight of
oxygen is about 16.

00:04:51.433 --> 00:04:53.867
The molecular weight of each
hydrogen atom is 1, so that

00:04:53.867 --> 00:04:55.467
adds up to 18.

00:04:55.467 --> 00:04:56.567
That's why I have it there.

00:04:56.567 --> 00:05:00.967
So I've brought that value down
into here, 462 for the

00:05:00.967 --> 00:05:01.700
gas constant.

00:05:01.700 --> 00:05:04.000
And then of course I had to
convert the temperature, which

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:07.600
was 20 Celsius, to Kelvin,
and that's what you get.

00:05:07.600 --> 00:05:08.900
And be sure to put units.

00:05:08.900 --> 00:05:10.567
Always have units on there.

00:05:10.567 --> 00:05:13.800
That'll be Pascals if you're
following the normal

00:05:13.800 --> 00:05:15.267
SI system of units.

00:05:15.267 --> 00:05:18.600
The relative humidity is the
ratio of the partial pressure

00:05:18.600 --> 00:05:21.500
of water vapor to the saturation
value at the

00:05:21.500 --> 00:05:28.367
